  <div class="row-fluid styleguide-notes">

    <div class="styleguide-wrapper">
      <div class="span12">
        <div class="content-container styleguide-container">
          <h1>Styleguide notes</h1>
          <hr />
          <h2>Page loading</h2>
          <hr />

          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>Displayed when ajax content is requested from server.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <p>Only common styles are loaded for this component.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common/loading.scss</p>
            <p>/common-components/product-variants.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Use of Javascript</h3>
            <p>Load messages are used to support the Ajax request functions to inform users that the server is currently processing a request.</p>
            <h4>Use of AJAX</h4>
            <p>Loading states should only be displayed whilst an Ajax request is in progress or has failed.</p>
            <h4>Non-JS behaviour</h4>
            <p>Non-js users should not see the loading animation state. They may receive error messages however if the page has returned in a state where the content can no be populated from the server side.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>The loading state is either in progress or returned as an error if the Ajax request fails. A sensible error message should be populated in the load message container if the ajax request fails. It appears in the product listing results and the product description product variants.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

